Sextus Julius Severus was a member of one of the most notable families in Roman Dalmatia, he served as Governor of Moesia and was appointed Governor of Britain in 131. According to Cassius Dio Sextus Julius Severus was the best Hadrian's general who suppressed the Jewish rebellion(Bar Kokhba revolt) in Judaea A.D. 135, the event that marked the beginning of the Jewish diaspora.\n